    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-02-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2023-05-09T14:28:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Fire Suppression and Response Funding Assurance</strong><strong> Act</strong></p> <p>This bill sets the federal cost share of fire management assistance at 75% of the eligible cost of such assistance and permits a state or local government to use such assistance for the predeployment of assets and resources.</p> <p>The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) must complete a rulemaking to provide criteria for the circumstances under which it may recommend that the President increase the federal cost share.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
